A

Arguments - Class in se.softhouse.jargo.addons
Additional Arguments.
To avoid explicitly specifying se.softhouse.jargo.addons.Arguments when using arguments from both jargo and jargo-addons you can use static imports for each method.

D

dateArgument(String...) - Static method in class se.softhouse.jargo.addons.Arguments
Creates an Argument that parses dates with the default timezone and the ISODateTimeFormat.dateOptionalTimeParser().
dateArgument(DateTimeZone, String...) - Static method in class se.softhouse.jargo.addons.Arguments
Creates an Argument that parses dates with the provided timezone.
